{
  "texts": [
    "In our study, the calculation of the CTR was based on the segmentation of both lungs and the heart in CXRs.",
    "In particular, we employed attention UNet to develop the deep model for the segmentation of both lungs and the heart, where the input image size was 512 × 512, the number of epochs was set to 100 and the batch size was set to 4.",
    "The initial learning rate was 0.00001; when the loss of the validation set increased for two consecutive epochs, the learning rate was reduced by half.",
    "Once the binary mask of both lungs and the heart was obtained, the thoracic diameter (L) and the cardiac diameter (L 1 + L 2) could be calculated by the proposed algorithm, where the process for doing so is described as follows.",
    "Step 1: The closed morphology operation was applied to the mask to eliminate holes and burrs."
  ]
}